## Overall Reflection

The biggest takeaway for me was that the most useful outputs were not necessarily the most impressive ones. The summarization task showed how quickly an LLM can reduce a dense reading into its key ideas, while the current-events task showed the importance of knowing what the model does not know. Across all five prompts, I found myself paying less attention to whether the model sounded confident and more attention to whether it understood the limits of its own knowledge. That seems particularly important when using AI in educational or professional settings.
